tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and low HbA1c. These findings suggest acute or chronic renal impairment and possible tubular dysfunction. The presence of glucosuria and ketonuria with normal blood glucose and low HbA1c may indicate renal glycosuria and possible non-diabetic ketosis. Urine abnormalities (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) may suggest underlying urinary tract pathology. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and clinical correlation.
